In a #bowl{}, combine the @flour{2%tbsp} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Put your @British turkey steaks{420%g} in between two sheets of #clingfilm{} and use
the back of a #frying pan{} to bash the turkey steaks, until they are no more than
1cm thick.

Tip: This is a great way to cut down on cooking time.

Coat each turkey steak in the flour mix, then place one or two slices of @Serrano
ham{1%slice} on the top side of each steak.

Roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{2} into quarters and set aside. Heat 2 tbsp of
@oil{2%tbsp} in a frying pan on medium heat, drop in three quarters of the
@sage{1%sprig} leaves and fry for ~{30%seconds} until just crisp. Immediately
remove the leaves from the pan and set aside.

Tip: Be careful not to let them burn!

Now add the @Netherend butter salted{3%tbsp} to the empty pan, allow it to melt, then
lay the turkey steaks in the frying pan (Serrano ham side up) and cook for
~{4-5%minutes} on each side until cooked and well browned. At the same time, add
2 tbsp of oil to another pan and add your mushrooms, season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and
a good grind of @pepper{} and cook for ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, boil a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Once your turkey and mushrooms are both ready, remove from the frying pans and set
aside. With the empty turkey frying pan on a low heat, pour in the
@white wine vinegar{2%tbsp}, @chicken stock pot{1} and @boiling water{200%ml},
stirring well to scrape all the lovely sticky bits from the bottom of the pan.

> This is called de-glazing.

Turn up the heat to medium and leave everything to bubble away until about half the
liquid is left.

While the liquid is reducing, put the @wheat tagliatelle{360%g} in the boiling water
for ~{6%minutes} or until 'al dente'.

Once the stock in the frying pan has reduced, stir in @crème fraîche{4%tbsp} and
return both the turkey, mushrooms and sage leaves to the pan to heat through.

Drain the pasta (reserving 2 tbsp of pasta water) and pop it in the pan with the
creamy mushroom sauce, together with the reserved pasta water.

Tip the pasta with its turkey and creamy mushroom sauce into #bowls{} and top with
a few torn sage leaves. Enjoy!